    commonDisputesPara: "The most common legal disputes in Minneapolis are family law (custody, divorce, domestic abuse orders for protection), landlord-tenant matters (eviction defense, habitability under Minnesota's Covenants of Habitability statute), personal injury (auto accidents on I-94/I-35W/494-694, slip-and-fall on icy sidewalks), employment law (wage theft, discrimination under the Minnesota Human Rights Act), and criminal defense.",
